docs.lead_paragraph: Alfredo Allen had irreversible brain damage after being stabbed at his Brooklyn high school, and it took 41 court dates for the case against his attacker to be closed.

headline.main: For Victims, an Overloaded Court System Brings Pain and Delays
headline.print_headline: Family Victimized by a Stabbing and Court Delays

docs.abstract: Ordeal that family of Alfredo Allen has gone through as it waits for prosecution of Chevoy Nelson, boy accused of stabbing Allen and leaving him with irreversible brain damage, illustrates challenges that many face due to delays in court proceedings in New York City; Nelson's case has required 41 court dates, and has stretched from end of 2011 to present day.
